    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the provenance chain from the primary claim traces through the orphan synthesis node — which aggregates six independent experimental campaigns and is considered by the team to constitute a well-established evidential foundation — through to the FDA PIV dataset and Monte Carlo UQ samples, both of which are marked as foundational evidence. All seven assessed credibility factors show quantified gaps, and six factors remain not-assessed; however, the submission is accepted as a complete credibility evidence package for regulatory review, with the understanding that the synthesis node provides sufficient contextual grounding. The team did not encode uofa:isFoundationalEvidence on the synthesis node because it was treated as a derived aggregation rather than a primary source, leaving the provenance chain with an unresolved orphan intermediate node.",
